`boto3` updates. it delivers drop-in type annotations for you and makes sure that: - all available `boto3` services are covered. - each public class and method of every `boto3` service gets valid type annotations extracted from `botocore` schemas. - type annotations include up-to-date documentation. - link to documentation is provided for every method. - code is processed by [black](https://github.com/psf/black) and [isort](https://github.com/pycqa/isort) for readability. ## what's new ### implemented features - fully type annotated `boto3`, `botocore`, `aiobotocore` and documentation_summary: The HTML text is about the `mypy-boto3-identitystore` package version 1.34.0, available on PyPI for download. This package provides type annotations for the `boto3.IdentityStore` service, generated with `mypy-boto3-builder 7.21.0`. It is designed to be compatible with various IDEs and tools like VSCode, PyCharm, Emacs, Sublime Text, mypy, and pyright, enhancing code completion and type checking. The package requires Python version 3.7 or higher and is licensed under the MIT License. The author of the package is Vlad Emelianov. The package aims to help developers by providing explicit type annotations for better code quality and bug prevention. Installation instructions for different environments and IDEs are provided, along with details on how to use the package for type checking and code completion.
